This paper deals with approximation algorithms for a graph optimization problem, specifically the metric {s,t}-path-TSP and shortest connected T-joins. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves mathematical optimization and linear programming, which could place it in the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses approximation ratios and analysis, which could also make it relevant to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
